	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> <date>June 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5614</date> <add>&#63;</add></p>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
				<p>Rev. Sir&#33;</p>
				<p>A friend of mine&#44; to whom I <sic>recommanded</sic> Your<lb/> valuable Periodical&#44; the Occt&#44; requests that I shall<lb/> beseech your Hon. to forward to his Address the<lb/> first No of the <sic>comming</sic> monthly Magazine and continue<lb/> to do so successively.  He is likewise desirous to<lb/> obtain of the same <sic>Magazin</sic> the Numbers of the<lb/> past <hi rend="underline">two years</hi>&#44; neatly Bound <hi rend="underline">in one Volume</hi>&#44;<lb/> wishing&#44; that you might have it in <sic>readness</sic>&#44; for<lb/> the next month&#44; when he anticipates having the<lb/> pleasure of <sic>caling</sic> with you and to settle the <sic>accont</sic>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">By the same opportunity&#44; I will feel obliged&#44;<lb/> if you will hand him the Papers&#44; containing Certificates<lb/> and Diploma&#44; of mine&#44; send you some time since with an<lb/> Article written <sic>intented</sic> as a reply to the <persName>Rev I. Rosenfeld</persName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your leading Art. against progressive Reform<lb/> in the <date>June</date> No has greatly pleased our friends here&#44; and<lb/> demands our respectful thanks&#44; while the strictures<lb/> against <persName>I. Wise</persName> <hi rend="underline">D. D.</hi> in Page 148. has paralyzed even some<lb/> of his best friends&#8212;such weapons so powerful and</p>
				<p rend="The following is written sideways in the left margin."></p>
				<p>V&#35; <persName>Mr N. Moses</persName>&#44;</p>
				<p>care of <persName>Hyman Moses &#38; Co.</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Cincinnati <sic>ohio</sic></placeName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>2</p>
				<p>so ably directed must <sic>eventualy</sic> prostrate that<lb/> great champion of Reform.  He is indeed miserably<lb/> humbled already&#44; doubtless there are many Persons<lb/> who would gladly take the Field&#44; but believing the<lb/> holding of him up to contempt is assigning him&#8212;<lb/><sic>to</sic> much importance&#44; he is however in proper hands<lb/> and nothing will afford &#40;true believers&#41; so much<lb/> gratification as a continuance of the <hi rend="underline">same</hi> and<lb/> which we have the <sic>assurrance</sic> is to follow &#8220;<add>Hebrew</add>&#8221;<lb/> &#33;&#8220;<add>Hebrew</add>&#8221;&#8212;The <hi rend="underline">D.D</hi> has established his <hi rend="underline">head&#45;quaters</hi><lb/> in the <hi rend="underline">Camp of the Blind</hi>&#33;  Hostilities commenced&#44; on<lb/> the past festivals&#44; when <hi rend="underline">he</hi> boldly attacked&#44; by<lb/> seizing the principles of our Ancient Formulas<lb/> Expelling&#44; <add>Hebrew</add> <hi rend="underline">Rush</hi>&#44; <add>Hebrew</add> Musaph&#45;Pajutims&#44; <add>Hebrew</add> Ackdumos&#44; &#38; some more<lb/> also he is preparing now a choir&#44; &#38; <del>intend</del> <sic>&#38;</sic> perhaps an<lb/> organ where this will end time alone will develop&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">This mistaken reform&#44; is a novelty&#44; particul<lb/>ary to Persons who have no mind of their own&#44;<lb/> will doubtless for a time be devoured by them<lb/> with avidity&#8212;but also vanish like every Phantom as<lb/> soon the <hi rend="underline">Light</hi> &#40;<persName>Dr Wise&#39;s</persName> weekly paper in <add>&#63;</add>&#41; will break on&#8212;<lb/> &#8220;<add>Hebrew</add>&#8221; and as our sages said &#8220;<add>Hebrew</add>&#8221;&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">&#33;<add>Hebrew</add>&#8221;&#44; The new&#45;born <hi rend="underline">Israelite</hi><lb/> Weekly Pap. By <persName>I. Weisse</persName> will make its first appearance<lb/> on the <date>1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> of July</date>&#8212;its motto is to be &#8220;&#33;<add>Hebrew</add>&#33;&#44;&#8221; &#40;ignis fatuus&#41;<lb/> and we might say&#44; with Jews. V. 20. <add>Hebrew</add>&#33; it may <hi rend="underline">probably</hi><lb/> enlighten the <sic>Gentils</sic> if it does not reform his <sic>Brethern</sic>.<lb/> I will take the liberty of sending you a number when published.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am Dr Sir&#44; with much esteem&#44; Your mo. ob. Sert</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Dr. I. Mayer</persName>.</p>
				<p rend="The following is written sideways in the left margin of the page."></p>
				<p>P. S. <add>Hebrew</add>&#33;  The <persName>Rev. I. Wise</persName> D. D. the<lb/> Antagonist of the <hi rend="underline">Kabalah</hi>&#44; the Adversirer of <hi rend="underline">Thalmud</hi><lb/> the <sic>Enemie</sic> of the Old obscure Rabbinism&#44; performed<lb/> to day a <hi rend="underline">Kabalistical Function</hi> <add>Hebrew</add> He <hi rend="underline">Benshd</hi><lb/> a Child&#44; which died&#44; while he was Benshing it&#8212;who is<lb/> the Hypocrite&#63;  O <persName>Moses</persName>&#33; O Tempora&#33;</p>
